                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14902666" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2015 13:53:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Initially my suspicion was that the conflict detection does not work in some edge case like a background read between a rebase and the commit of the changes. However, it turns out there is another problem introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2829&quot; title=&quot;Comparing node states for external changes is too slow&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2829&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2829&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The cache invalidation based on journal entries does not work reliably. The issue occurs when a background read picks up changes from another cluster node, before the background update pushes local changes to a journal entry. The id of the journal entry is derived from the current head revision instead of the most recent _lastRev entry. This means, later a background read on another cluster node  will not have its caches invalided properly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14902671" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2015 13:57:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added (ignored) test to trunk: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1704629&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1704629&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14902805" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2015 15:30:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in trunk: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1704655&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1704655&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14904223" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 23 Sep 2015 09:16:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged into 1.2 branch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1704781&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1704781&lt;/a&gt; and 1.0 branch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1704792&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1704792&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
